-- Pirates Seize Taiwanese Fishing Boat Off Coast of Mauritius, Express Says
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2010-10-07T07:00:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/pirates-seize-taiwanese-fishing-boat-off-coast-of-mauritius-express-says.html
A Taiwanese fishing vessel was
captured by suspected pirates off the coast of Mauritius,
 l’Express  reported, citing Prime Minister  Navin Ramgoolam .  The ship was seized 200 kilometers (124 miles) north of the
Indian Ocean island and its captors have asked for a ransom, the
Port Louis-based newspaper said. The boat holds a fishing permit
issued by the Mauritian authorities, it said.  The vessel hasn’t been in contact with its Taiwanese owners
since Oct. 4, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Kamlesh Bhuckory  in Port Louis via Johannesburg at
   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin in Johannesburg at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 